cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on analyzing the performance of pre-trained convolutional neural networks on object detection and related tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper involves training and fine-tuning neural networks, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the features and activations of neural networks, which could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves analyzing large datasets, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
